adverbs.description: unsympathizingly (comparative more unsympathizingly, superlative most unsympathizingly)

examples: No Northern forest, rude and gloomy with pines, stood stiffly and unsympathizingly watching the graceful water, but cheerful groves and delicate coppices opened in vistas where level sunlight streamed, and barred the river with light, between belts of lightsome shadow.
